Body: Yep. Their investors are guaranteed a limited downside risk thanks to the whisky portfolio. Whisky is a perfect asset for this, since it ensures a more crisis proof and diverse portfolio than having only oil or real estate assets in your investment portfolio. Author: Skitlslover
Title: [ANN] WHISKYTOKEN The First Whisky Based Cryptotoken
Body: Can you elaborate on this asset-backed mechanism you have just mentioned? How can we benefit from it?

Author: miamicrp
Title: [ANN] WHISKYTOKEN The First Whisky Based Cryptotoken
Body: What happens if the token is worth less than the portfolio? After a successful ICO, the asset-backed mechanism is scheduled to come into force as soon as the asset-backed value (90% of the whisky portfolio value) has reached the value of the initial market capitalisation (after the ICO has ended), i.e. 100% coverage. If the market capitalisation is subsequently below the asset-backed value for one month, a buy-back is made. To this end, a part of the high-end whisky portfolio will initially be sold. From this proceeds, purchase orders are placed on the stock exchanges until the market capitalization is again above the asset-backed value. The tokens acquired through the asset-backed mechanism are destroyed in order to guarantee a sustained deflation and an increase of the value of WHISKY TOKEN

Author: johntravolta63
Title: [ANN] WHISKYTOKEN The First Whisky Based Cryptotoken
Body: Checked about implementation - 3 years after ICO. As for working principles, if the market capitalization is subsequently below the asset-backed value for a period of one month, WHISKY TOKEN is repurchased by the WHYTOKEN GmbH until the market capitalization is above the asset-backed value again (buy-back). For this purpose, a portion of the high-end whisky portfolio corresponding to the buy-back will be liquidated initially. From this revenue, purchase orders are placed on the stock exchanges, resulting in an increase in market capitalization. The tokens acquired in this way are destroyed in order to guarantee a deflation and thus a sustainable increase in value

Body: The Cicones  Odysseus and his legion set sail from Troy aboard twelve ships. Tranquil waters facilitated the movement of the ships and they were well out to sea. After a few days, they sighted land and Eurylochus, second-in-command to Odysseus, convinced him to weigh anchor, go ashore and devastate the city with the assurance that they would not be harmed. Seeing the ships weigh anchor and thenceforth the warriors coming ashore, the Ciconians, the local residents, fled to the nearby mountains. Odysseus and his men plundered and looted the empty city. However, the men of Odysseus resisted his efforts to get them back aboard the ship immediately and after a hearty meal accompanied by wine that flew like water, they fell asleep on the shore. Before the first light, the Ciconians returned with their fierce neighbors and set upon the warriors, killing as many as they could. Odysseus and his men beat a hasty retreat to their ships but heavy damages had already been inflicted on their number. Berating himself for having listened to Eurylochus and thereafter losing so many valuable men, Odysseus and Eurylochus fought with each other but they were separated by their fellow-men and peace was once again established amidst the warriors.

Body: In total, there are three major problems:  1. Volatility of cryptocurrencies: Cryptocurrencies are only seldom covered with substance values. As a result, prices quickly collapse when demand falls, threatening investors with a total loss. The team limited downside risk. The risk of loss for WHISKY TOKEN holders is minimized by the real high-end whisky portfolio. Thus, there is a fall arrest protection against total course breakdowns. At the same time, price gains of the token are not limited by the high-end whisky portfolio.

Author: gt89_ups
Title: [ANN] WHISKYTOKEN The First Whisky Based Cryptotoken
Body: 2. Expensive entry barriers: Retail investors cannot benefit from the rarest whiskies for two reasons. Firstly, the minimum investment amounts for participation in alternative investment funds are several tens of thousands of euros. Secondly, the creation of a small whisky portfolio by a retail investor would involve not only high investments but also high risks due to a lack of diversification. The team made low entry barrier.  Participation in the WHISKY TOKEN crowdsale is available for as little as EUR 30.

Author: gt89_ups
Title: [ANN] WHISKYTOKEN The First Whisky Based Cryptotoken
Body: 3. Enormous costs for intermediaries: Alternative investment funds have various management fees and running costs that have a negative impact on returns. Investors are thus deprived of a not inconsiderable portion of their profits. WHY is almost free of any commission.  Through the use of blockchain technology and the distinction to traditional investment funds running costs are significantly reduced. Management fees do not exist. This increases the return of all WHISKY TOKEN holders.  Check the White Paper carefully again next time

Author: OfficialWhiskytoken
Title: [ANN] WHISKYTOKEN The First Whisky Based Cryptotoken
Body: We calculated that we may generate an average net return of 9% p.a.. If this is the case the asset backed mechanism could be activated in a year, starting from the end of the ICO.  Quote from: Z1pp4 on November 14, 2018, 08:20:39 AM I can only imagine the mass adoption of this token. For instance, if you want to buy a bottle of lets say my favorite Caol Ila, you have to pay taxes. If you import spirits, you will still have to pay excise to your local tax office. How it is going to work wit this coin?  Thats true we still have to pay taxes. But we already considered this in our calculations. The cost though is pretty high but not as substantial as it would break our business model. So in germany we have to pay 13,03€ per liter of pure alcohol so a 700ml bottle with 40% is going to cost us 3,65€ in Taxes. Since we are targeting high end whiskies the percentage "lost" diminishes the pricier the whisky gets. So if we bought Whisky for 30€ per bottle, the tax alone would cost us 12.1% of the value of the whisky. A 200€ bottle, however, only 1.825%
